list.item:
Even technical contact with GDR
                                would tarnish our prestige with West Berliners and West Germans and
                                would lessen their resolve to stand firm;

Mission judges, in light of Deptel 236 to Berlin, 1012 to Bonn,Document 45.
                                that it would be very difficult to persuade British to draw a line
                                once they go so far as to have technical contacts;
